{
  "texts": [
    "VAs extract the essence of users' needs in the format of 6W1H (when, where, who, whom, why, what, how) from users' spontaneous speech.",
    "For example, the need expressed as \"Since the students seem sleepy, I would like to play music that can help concentrate via a video streaming service in the laboratory after lunch,\" can be structurally represented using the 6W1H framework as follows:• how: Video streaming service; • where: Laboratory; • when: After lunch;• what: Music conducive to concentration; • whom: Students;• why: The students appear sleepy.VAs engage in dialogue to elicit potential needs by asking if anything is lacking.",
    "The how component directly indicates the name of the service the user wishes to use.",
    "VAs extract temporal data on needs by aligning closely with users' daily lives.",
    "A limitation of prior research is that it can only extract needs related to existing services with known service names, failing to identify needs for new or unknown services."
  ]
}